  "prompt": "Is Star Wars: The Old Republic for Mac?",
  "response": "No, Star Wars: The Old Republic (SWTOR) is not natively available for macOS.\n\nHowever, there are ways to play it on a Mac:\n\n*   **Boot Camp:** You can install Windows on a partition of your Mac's hard drive using Boot Camp Assistant. This allows you to dual-boot between macOS and Windows. Once you have Windows installed, you can install and play SWTOR as you would on a PC. This generally offers the best performance.\n*   **Virtualization Software (e.g., Parallels Desktop, VMware Fusion):** These programs allow you to run Windows within macOS. While convenient, this method often results in lower performance than Boot Camp.\n*   **GeForce Now:** As of my last update, Star Wars: The Old Republic (SWTOR) is available on Geforce Now. This means you can stream SWTOR without needing to install it locally.\n\nSo, while there's no native Mac version, you have options to play it. Boot Camp usually provides the best performance, but virtualization and cloud gaming are easier if you don't want to install Windows directly.",
